.START 

EG&G Inc. said it received a six-year $250 million contract from the National Science Foundation in a joint venture with a unit of Ashland Oil Inc. of Ashland, Ky. 

EG&G, Wellesley, Mass., a maker of scientific instruments and parts, has a 40% stake in the venture, called Antarctic Support Associates. 

Antarctic Support will provide logistical and operational support for scientific research projects in Antarctica, including maintenance of vehicles and equipment at U.S. Antarctic stations and field camps. 

The joint contract with Holmes & Narver Services Inc., of Orange, Calif., includes a four-year option which could raise the contract value to $500 million. 

Holmes & Narver is an operations and maintenance services company that specializes in remote-site operations. 

